  "decision_conditions": [
    "The proposed conversion of the ballroom by reason of the subdivision of the first floor and the poorly designed and detailed mezzanine floors would cause substantial harm to the character, appearance and significance of the Grade II Listed Building and would be contrary to the Planning (Listed Buildings and Conservation Areas) Act 1990, National Planning Policy Framework Section 16, London Plan (2016) Policies 7.6 and 7.8, Draft London Plan (December 2019) Policy HC1 and Ealing Development Management DPD (2013) Policy 7C. | The proposed development fails to demonstrate that the loss of significance and substantial harm to the heritage assets is justified through securing substantial public benefits neither has it been demonstrated that the significance of the heritage asset cannot be secured by alternative less harmful uses or through granting funding or not for profit charitable ownership contrary to the Planning (Listed Buildings and Conservation Areas) Act 1990, National Planning Policy Framework Section 16, London Plan (2016) Policy 7.8, Draft London Plan (December 2019) Policy HC1 and Ealing Development Management DPD (2013) Policy 7C."
